In a mixing bowl, cream shortening and sugars. Beat in eggs, milk, coffee granules and vanilla. Combine the flour, cocoa, baking soda and salt; add to the creamed mixture and mix well. Stir in pecans, chips, raisins and coconut. Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls 2 in. apart onto ungreased baking sheets. Bake at 375 degrees F for 10-12 minutes.